article.headline: Oral Roberts 89, Austin Peay 80
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. -- Dominique Morrison scored 21 points and Kevin Ford had 19 for Oral Roberts, which came on strong in the second half to defeat Austin Peay 89-80 on Saturday night. The Golden Eagles (17-12) shot 65.5 percent (19-for-29) in the second half after trailing 36-31 at halftime of the nonconference game. Oral Roberts took the lead for good with a 17-7 run that made it 50-44 with 12:50 to play. The Governors (16-13) trailed by three, 65-62, with 5:38 left, but Warren Niles, who finished with 18 points, hit a 3-pointer for Oral Roberts and Ford added a layup to make it 70-62. Morrison and Niles both scored 14 of their points in the second half, and Ford scored 13 of his. Michael Craion added 16 points and 12 rebounds for Oral Roberts. Wes Channels scored 25 points and John Fraley had 11 points and 11 rebounds to lead Austin Peay.
